## SLIDE 2 — Brief Project Description

**What is DeceptiCloud?**

DeceptiCloud is an AI-powered cyber deception platform that protects cloud-hosted web applications by intelligently detecting cyberattacks and luring attackers into convincing fake environments (honeypots), while keeping real systems completely secure.

**The Core Idea:**
- Every incoming HTTP request passes through an AI gateway
- Machine Learning classifies it as benign or malicious in real time
- Malicious requests are silently rerouted to honeypots
- The attacker interacts with a fake system, revealing their techniques
- All activity is logged to a tamper-proof blockchain for evidence

**One-line summary:**
> *"We deceive the attacker before they can deceive us."*

---

## SLIDE 3 — Problem Statement

**Why does this project matter?**

- Cyberattacks cost the global economy **$8 trillion in 2023** (Cybersecurity Ventures)
- Traditional security (firewalls, IDS/IPS) only **block** attacks — they do not **study** them
- Attackers probe systems repeatedly, improving their techniques each time
- No existing open-source system combines **ML detection + LLM deception + blockchain evidence** in one platform
- Cloud-hosted systems are especially vulnerable due to public exposure

**The Gap:**
> Existing tools detect attacks. DeceptiCloud detects, deceives, documents, and learns.

