### Brief Purpose of Each Module

1. **AI Routing Proxy** — Central intelligence gateway. Classifies every HTTP request using ML + rules and forwards malicious traffic to honeypots silently.

2. **ML Model API** — Hosts retrained Web Attack Detection (v2, 93.97% balanced accuracy) and DDoS Detection (v2, 99.9% accuracy) models as REST endpoints for real-time inference.

3. **LLM Response Engine** — Uses Ollama (local LLM) to generate unique, convincing fake response pages for each attack type — SQL errors, fake passwd files, reflected XSS confirmations.

4. **GAN Synthetic Data Generator** — Generates 35 realistic fake user profiles per honeypot database using CTGAN, making honeypots indistinguishable from real systems.

5. **Blockchain Ledger** — Writes every attack event as an immutable SHA-256 block. Tamper detection built-in — modifying any block breaks the entire chain hash.

6. **Real-Time SOC Dashboard** — Web-based Security Operations Center interface. 9 panels covering attacks, health (17 services), LLM stats, GAN data, blockchain, canary tokens, and behavioral fingerprints.

7. **Canary Token System** — Embeds fake high-value URLs (`.env`, `backup.sql`, `wp-admin`) in honeypot responses. Any access to these triggers a high-priority alert — reveals attacker reconnaissance intent.

8. **Behavioral Fingerprinting Engine** — Builds a behavioral hash per attacker based on attack sequences, timing, tools used. Clusters similar attackers to attribute multiple attacks to one threat actor.

9. **K8s Auto-Recovery Watchdog** — Background process that polls honeypot ports every 2 seconds. If a honeypot crashes (e.g., under DDoS), it restarts the Flask process automatically — mimicking Kubernetes ReplicaSet behavior.

10. **Dynamic Honeypot System** — The overarching deception layer (ports 4001–4007). Unlike static honeypots, these 7 Flask applications change their content, responses, and data dynamically using LLM + GAN + ML routing + Canary Tokens + Behavioral Fingerprinting together. Explained in detail on the next slide.

