## SLIDE 11 — New Component: Canary Tokens & Behavioral Fingerprinting

**Canary Tokens:**
- Hidden "tripwire" URLs embedded in honeypot responses
- Examples: `/backup.sql`, `/.env`, `/wp-admin`, `/.git/config`
- When an attacker clicks/requests these, an alert is triggered
- Reveals: the attacker is doing reconnaissance beyond just SQL injection
- 8 canary token types deployed across all 7 honeypots

**Behavioral Fingerprinting:**
- Tracks every attacker's IP across multiple requests
- Builds a behavioral profile: which attack types they use, in what order, timing patterns
- Assigns a unique [behavioral_hash](file:///media/amei-302/New%20Volume/SEMESTER%20VIII/Ahmed%20Fype-II/honeypot/behavioral_fingerprint.py#57-76) per attacker profile
- Clusters similar attackers (same tool, same methodology)
- Useful for attributing multiple attacks from different IPs to the same threat actor

